The article strongly disagrees with the decision to downgrade the United States' ratings by Fitch. It argues that the ratings model declined under President Trump but improved under President Biden, and it is unrealistic to downgrade the US at a time when Biden has achieved a strong economic recovery. The article also suggests that Republican officials' extremism, such as supporting default, undermining governance and democracy, and advocating for tax cuts for the wealthy and corporations, poses a threat to the economy.